  "response": "Michael Jordan did not actually grow taller after he reached adulthood. He is widely reported to be 6 feet 6 inches (198 cm) tall. Height is primarily determined by genetics, and most people reach their maximum height in their late teens or early twenties when their growth plates close. \n\nWhile there is no scientifically proven method to significantly increase height after this period, some athletes may appear taller due to their posture, fitness, and training. Strengthening core muscles and improving posture can lead to a more elongated appearance. For Jordan, his height, combined with his athleticism and skill, contributed to his success as a basketball player. If you're curious about his training regimen or career achievements, feel free to ask!",
